<HTML>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<TITLE>JOHN SWEENEY -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>JOHN SWEENEY</H3>
<HR>
<B>POLICY ANALYST, LATIN AMERICA</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/sweeney.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Sweeney examines the advantages of further expanding free trade throughout the Americas, beginning with Chile, Venezuela and Argentina. Sweeney is the founder and long-time editor of the influential Venezuelan newsletter Ven Economy, and a former publisher of a bi-weekly newsletter, Andes/Mexico Insight. He also reported on Latin American affairs for the Journal of Commerce, Business Week, Newsweek, The International Herald Tribune, among others. Sweeney,   who   served   as  a   consultant   for   major   U.S. corporations in Latin America, has written speeches for past Venezuelan presidents. He is a graduate of Kent State University.

