<HEAD>
    <TITLE>BLAST FORM THE PAST</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="lttrhead.gif">
<H1><CENTER><TT>BLAST FROM THE PAST</TT></CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="slidbar.gif" WIDTH="398" HEIGHT="4" ALIGN="BOTTOM"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Periodically Disovery features articles and essays from the Discovery
archives that highlight timely, important, public policy issues. Check these
pages often to catch the latest, oldest articles.</H3>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3><CENTER><IMG SRC="slidbar.gif" WIDTH="398" HEIGHT="4" ALIGN="BOTTOM"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></CENTER>
</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H1><A HREF="gingrich.html">Gingrich and Clinton develop transactional politics</A>
</H1>
&quot;Especially today, more national officials need to notch down their
interest-group checkmarking and try out the Gingrich/Clinton model: BE real
in your major addresses, and GET real with some of your otherwise demanding
audiences. Float a deal -- not a petty one, but exalting: &quot;I will stick
my neck out for you here, but I expect a helping hand to transform this
issue afterward, for America.&quot;<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H5>From September 1995 <I>The Web Chronicle</I></H5>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<H1><CENTER><A HREF="aboutdis.html"><IMG SRC="aboutdis.gif" WIDTH="107"
