<title>Straight Talk From the Family Research Council</title>

<body background="/townhall/FRC/images/bckgnd1.gif" text="#3300ff" link="#ee0000" 
vlink="#000000">

<img src="/townhall/FRC/net/strttalk.jpg" align=left width=350 height=250 hspace=12 
vspace=3>

<strong><font size=3>
<i>It's time to hear what we have to say -- our perspective, our words,   
unedited...</i>
<p>
<font size=4><i>Straight Talk from the Family Research Council</i></font> 
premiered on NET (National Empowerment Television) on Wednesday, November 
1, 1995 at 8:00 pm. 
<p>
This new, weekly, one-hour show presents viewers with a clear perspective 
on issues facing families today.  Not only will we inform you of government 
policies affecting families across the nation, but we'll equip you with tools for 
shaping those policies.  So make sure to tune in!
<p>
NET currently reaches into more than 11 million homes and is growing 
daily! To see if you can receive the network in your area, check the 
<a href="/townhall/FRC/net/netlist.html.cgi">station list</a>.
<p>
In case you missed a broadcast, or if you can't receive the show in your area, we 
have made the transcripts from each show available below for your convenience.

<a name="episodes">
<p><hr size=3 noshade><p>

<center><h2><i>Straight Talk</i> Transcripts</h2></center>

<dl>
<dt><a href="/townhall/FRC/net/nov95.html">November, 1995</a>
<dt><a href="/townhall/FRC/net/dec95.html">December, 1995</a>
<dt><a href="/townhall/FRC/net/jan96.html">January, 1996</a>
<dt><a href="/townhall/FRC/net/feb96.html">February, 1996</a>
<dt><a href="/townhall/FRC/net/mar96.html">March, 1996</a>
