<title>Reproducing FRC Publications</title>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center><h2>Reproducing FRC Publications</h2></center>

<font size=4>

We are pleased that you find our publications to be valuable 
resources and that you are interested in sharing them with
others who are concerned about the well-being of the traditional
family.

<p>

You may reprint any FRC publication, subject to the following 
conditions:

<p><ul>

<li>The item excerpted must be taken in full and without alteration,
unless it can be condensed without altering its meaning and such
condensation is noted.
<p>
<li>Full attribution must be made to the Family Research Council (and
<I>Washington Watch</I>, <i>Ed Facts</i>, or whatever source you used)
and the attribution should include the date of the item and the
author, if noted in the publication.
<p>
<li>Please include the location of our Internet site:  http://www.frc.org
<p>
<li>The Family Research Council provides its publications to citizens
upon request.  There is no &quot;subscription&quot; cost, but
freewill donations to support the publications are accepted. 
Space permitting, we ask that reprints of items from our materials
be accompanied by this information about the availability of our
publications.  This information should include the address of
the Family Research Council (700 Thirteenth Street, NW, Washington,
DC, Suite 500, 20005) and our toll-free number (1-800-225-4008).

</ul><p>

Provided these conditions are followed, it is not necessary for
you or your organization to contact the Council each time a similar 
reprint is contemplated.

<p>

Bulk copies of <I>Washington Watch</I>, <I>Family Policy</I>,
and other FRC publications are also generally available at reduced
rates.  In the event that you contemplate a large distribution
of materials, it may prove more cost effective to procure multiple
copies from FRC.  Please contact an FRC representative at 1-800-225-4008
to discuss this option.

<p>

Again, thank you for your interest in our publications and your
desire to serve the pro-family cause.

<p></font><hr><p>

<center>
<a href="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrip.map">
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrip.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
<br>

