<P><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" size="-1">
<h5><a href="/townhall/events/welcome.html.cgi/textonly">[Text View]</a></h5>
<A HREF="/townhall/events/addevent.html.cgi">Submit</a> your event for posting.

<p>
<h4>Important events today in Conservative history:</h4>

<b>

</b>
<p> 
 
<HR WIDTH=50%>
<p>


<P>
<h3>1997</h3>
<p><b>January 8, 1996.</b> <a href="/heritage">Heritage Foundation</a> Lecture:
 <i>The Impending Storm: Why America Is Unprepared For Its Next War</i> featuring <b>Casper Weinberger</b>, former Secretary of Defense and co-author, <i>The Next War</i>. 12:00 noon,  reservations requested. Contact <a href="mailto:eftinkb@heritage.org">Brian Eftink</a> at (202) 675-1752.
 
<P><b>January 10-12, 1997.</b> National Taxpayers Conference. Organized by the National Taxpayers Union Foundation and Iowan for Tax Relief. Contact Cathi Smith, 703-683-5700.
<p><b>January 13, 1997.</b> <a href="/heritage">Heritage Foundation</a> Lecture: <i>Killing Us With Kindness: How Liberal Compassion Hurts</i> featuring <b>Don Feder</b>, Syndicated Columnist, <i>The Boston Herald</i>. 12:00 noon, reservations requested. Contact <a href="mailto:eftinkb@heritage.org">Brian Eftink</a> at (202) 675-1752.    
<p><b>January 17-18, 1997.</b> Long Beach, CA The Institute will hold a "Future of California" conference. Watch this
space for more details on the program. 
<p><b>February 12, 1997.</b>Washington, DC The Institute will conduct a Lincoln Day Colloquium in the nation's
capital. Keynote speaker to be announced. Contact Julie Ann Kessler for more information. 
<p><b>June 27-July 3, 1997.</b>Hong Kong The Institute will lead a Hong Kong trip to observe the historic
transition of power from Great Britain to the People's Republic of China. Truly a once in a lifetime experience. Watch this space for
more details. 
<P>

<br>
